---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { loadStats } from '../lib/stats';
import { formatBytes, formatNumber } from '../lib/ssr';
import ReadingLayout from '../components/ReadingLayout.vue';

const stats = loadStats();

const cards = [
  {
    href: '/docs/pipeline',
    eyebrow: 'How',
    title: 'Build pipeline',
    body: `How ${formatNumber(stats.unicode.assignedCodepointCount)} glyphs from ${stats.donorCount} donors become one TrueType Collection — the assembly line, plane partitioning, and why no glyph is ever hand-drawn.`,
  },
  {
    href: '/docs/sources',
    eyebrow: 'Where · glyphs',
    title: 'Where the glyphs come from',
    body: 'The donor strategy: 38 OFL-compatible donors, the Tier 1/2/3 sourcing model, code-chart SVG extraction for blocks no font covers, and why Full-Sung (Taiwan 全宋體) is the CJK donor instead of Noto Sans CJK.',
  },
  {
    href: '/docs/formats',
    eyebrow: 'Where · build',
    title: 'Output formats & distribution',
    body: 'The build emits four shapes: OTC (canonical), per-plane TTFs (legacy + PDF), per-plane WOFF2s (web embed), per-block WOFF2 subsets (this site). Plus the release pipeline: tag → CI → GitHub Release → website.',
  },
  {
    href: '/docs/specification',
    eyebrow: 'What · structure',
    title: 'Font specification',
    body: 'The internal structure of Essenfont-Regular.otc — faces, UPM strategy, per-face vertical metrics, and donor attribution. All values data-driven from the actual OTC file via SVG diagrams.',
  },
  {
    href: '/docs/coverage',
    eyebrow: 'What · status',
    title: 'Coverage, gaps & roadmap',
    body: 'What works, what\'s blocked on upstream fontisan fixes, what Chrome\'s OpenType Sanitizer actually enforces, and what\'s next.',
  },
];
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Engineering — Essenfont"
  description="Why Essenfont exists, how it is built from 38 donor fonts, where it ships, and what is on the roadmap. The full engineering story across four sub-pages."
  canonical="/docs"
>
  <ReadingLayout client:visible>
    <article class="engineering-hub">
    <header class="page-head">
      <h1>The whole story, in four pages</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Essenfont is one font that tries to cover every assigned Unicode 17 codepoint — {formatNumber(stats.unicode.assignedCodepointCount)} of them — using only OFL-licensed donor glyphs. The engineering story has four moving parts: <strong>why</strong> it exists, <strong>how</strong> it is built, <strong>where</strong> the glyphs come from, and <strong>where</strong> users can get it.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="stats-grid">
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-num">{formatNumber(stats.unicode.assignedCodepointCount)}</div>
        <div class="stat-cap">Assigned Unicode {stats.unicode.version} codepoints</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-num">{stats.unicode.blockCount}</div>
        <div class="stat-cap">Unicode blocks covered</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-num">{stats.donorCount}</div>
        <div class="stat-cap">Donor fonts assembled</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-num">5</div>
        <div class="stat-cap">Plane subfonts in the OTC</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-num">{formatBytes(stats.fontBinaries.otcSizeBytes)}</div>
        <div class="stat-cap">Canonical OTC on disk</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-num">{stats.websiteSubsets.woff2Count}</div>
        <div class="stat-cap">Per-block WOFF2 subsets served here</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="prose" data-reading-article>
      <aside class="user-callout">
        <strong>Just want to install or embed Essenfont?</strong>
        Skip ahead to the <a href="/docs/usage">How to use</a> guide — it walks you through which format fits (OTC, per-plane TTF, per-plane WOFF2, per-block WOFF2), with code, considerations, and a decision matrix. This Engineering section is for readers who want to understand <em>how the font is built</em>, not how to consume it.
      </aside>

      <h2>Why Essenfont exists</h2>
      <p>
        Every operating system ships a "last-resort" fallback font — the box with a hex codepoint inside it (<span class="tofu">□</span>, called <em>tofu</em>) that appears when no installed font covers a character. The Unicode Consortium maintains the <a href="https://github.com/unicode-org/last-resort-font" rel="noopener">Last Resort Font</a> for exactly this purpose, but it only ships tofu boxes — no real glyphs. Essenfont exists to be the fallback that <em>actually renders the character</em> instead of its hex label.
      </p>
      <p>
        Three constraints made this harder than it sounds:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>The glyph cap.</strong> A single OpenType face can hold at most 65,535 glyphs (16-bit glyph IDs). Unicode 17 has {formatNumber(stats.unicode.assignedCodepointCount)} assigned codepoints — roughly 2.5× the cap. A single TTF is physically impossible.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Redistribution.</strong> A universal fallback must be freely redistributable: bundled with OSes, embedded in PDFs, shipped in software. Every donor glyph has to be cleared for OFL redistribution, or the whole font is poisoned.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Authorship.</strong> Designing {formatNumber(stats.unicode.assignedCodepointCount)} glyphs by hand is a multi-decade project no one has finished. Canonical donor fonts (Noto, Full-Sung, etc.) already cover every assigned script authoritatively. Duplicating their work would either waste effort or introduce inconsistency. Essenfont's job is assembly, not authorship.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The result is one OpenType Collection with five plane subfonts, each under the cap, stitched from {stats.donorCount} donor fonts, and redistributable under OFL (with the non-commercial FSung restriction carried forward programmatically — see <a href="/docs/sources">/docs/sources</a>).
      </p>

      <h2>Compared to Last Resort Font</h2>
      <table class="comparison">
        <thead>
          <tr><th></th><th>Last Resort Font</th><th>Essenfont</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><th scope="row">Glyph source</th><td>Hand-drawn tofu boxes (hex codepoint label)</td><td>Vector outlines from {stats.donorCount} donor fonts</td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">Coverage</th><td>Unicode 16</td><td>Unicode 17 (incl. Sidetic, Beria Erfe, Tai Yo, Egyptian Hieroglyphs Extended-B)</td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">CJK</th><td>Noto Sans CJK (partial)</td><td>Full-Sung (Taiwan 全宋體) — every CJK extension through Unicode 17 Ext J</td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">License</th><td>OFL</td><td>OFL + FSung non-commercial restriction, propagated to <code>name</code> table</td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">Web embed</th><td>No</td><td>Per-plane and per-block WOFF2s</td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">Output format</th><td>Single TTF in repo</td><td>OTC (5 faces) + per-plane TTFs + WOFF2s, distributed via GitHub Releases</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Read deeper</h2>
    </section>

    <nav class="card-grid">
      {cards.map(c => (
        <a href={c.href} class="card">
          <span class="card-eyebrow">{c.eyebrow}</span>
          <h3 class="card-title">{c.title}</h3>
          <p class="card-body">{c.body}</p>
          <span class="card-cta">read →</span>
        </a>
      ))}
    </nav>

    <section class="prose">
      <p class="see-also">
        For the registry of every donor font and its license, see <a href="/donors">/donors</a>. For glyph-by-glyph attribution, see <a href="/provenance">/provenance</a>. For install and CSS embed instructions, see <a href="/docs">/docs</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
  </ReadingLayout>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.engineering-hub {
  max-width: 880px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 4rem 1.5rem 6rem;
}
.page-head { margin-bottom: 3rem; }

h1 {
  font-family: var(--spec-font-display);
  font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
  line-height: 1.1;
  margin: 0 0 1rem;
  color: var(--ef-text);
}
.lede {
  font-size: 1.125rem;
  line-height: 1.6;
  color: var(--ef-text);
  opacity: 0.85;
}
.stats-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr));
  gap: 1.5rem;
  margin: 3rem 0;
  padding: 2rem 0;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--ef-text);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ef-text);
}
.stat { text-align: left; }
.stat-num {
  font-family: var(--spec-font-display);
  font-size: 2.5rem;
  line-height: 1;
  color: var(--ef-rose, #bf4e6a);
}
.stat-cap {
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  margin-top: 0.5rem;
  color: var(--ef-text);
  opacity: 0.7;
}
.prose { margin-top: 1rem; }
.prose h2 {
  font-family: var(--spec-font-display);
  font-size: 1.75rem;
  margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
}
.prose p, .prose li {
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  font-size: 1.0625rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
  color: var(--ef-text);
}
.prose a {
  color: var(--ef-rose, #bf4e6a);
  text-decoration: underline;
  text-underline-offset: 3px;
}
.prose code {
  font-family: var(--spec-font-mono);
  background: rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
  padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
  border-radius: 3px;
  font-size: 0.9em;
}
.prose .tofu {
  display: inline-block;
  font-family: var(--spec-font-mono);
  border: 1px solid currentColor;
  padding: 0 0.35em;
  font-size: 0.9em;
  opacity: 0.6;
}
.user-callout {
  padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
  background: rgba(191, 78, 106, 0.08);
  border-left: 3px solid var(--ef-rose, #bf4e6a);
  margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
  font-size: 0.92rem;
  line-height: 1.6;
}
.user-callout a { color: var(--ef-rose, #bf4e6a); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
.user-callout strong { color: var(--ef-rose, #bf4e6a); }
.comparison {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  font-size: 0.92rem;
  margin: 1rem 0 2rem;
}
.comparison th, .comparison td {
  text-align: left;
  padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(128,128,128,0.2);
  vertical-align: top;
}
.comparison thead th {
  font-family: var(--spec-font-mono);
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  color: var(--ef-text);
  opacity: 0.7;
}
.comparison tbody th { font-weight: 600; opacity: 0.85; }
.comparison td code { font-size: 0.85em; }

.card-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
  gap: 1rem;
  margin: 1.5rem 0 3rem;
}
.card {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  border: 1px solid rgba(128,128,128,0.25);
  border-radius: 4px;
  text-decoration: none;
  color: inherit;
  transition: border-color 0.15s, transform 0.15s;
}
.card:hover {
  border-color: var(--ef-rose, #bf4e6a);
  transform: translateY(-1px);
}
.card-eyebrow {
  font-family: var(--spec-font-mono);
  font-size: 0.7rem;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  color: var(--ef-rose, #bf4e6a);
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}
.card-title {
  font-family: var(--spec-font-display);
  font-size: 1.2rem;
  margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
}
.card-body {
  font-size: 0.92rem;
  line-height: 1.55;
  opacity: 0.8;
  margin: 0 0 1rem;
  flex: 1;
}
.card-cta {
  font-family: var(--spec-font-mono);
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  color: var(--ef-rose, #bf4e6a);
}
.see-also {
  font-size: 0.92rem !important;
  opacity: 0.75 !important;
  padding-top: 1rem;
  border-top: 1px solid rgba(128,128,128,0.2);
}
</style>
